1772982000	SearXNG	https://labunix.xyz/posts/searxng/	<p>Every search query you type into Google, Bing, or DuckDuckGo is logged, profiled, and used to build a picture of you. Even privacy-focused search engines that promise not to track you are still a centralised service you have to trust. SearXNG removes that dependency — it&rsquo;s a metasearch engine that runs on your own server, aggregates results from multiple sources, and keeps your queries entirely private. Nobody sees what you&rsquo;re searching for except you.</p>\n<p>Private — accessible over WireGuard only.</p>	html	https://labunix.xyz/posts/searxng/			
